text:
Vegetarian food stall in neighborhood food court. Tried the vegetarian mee siam. The Zai Er (fried bean curd) and "chicken drumstick" were good but found the mee siam abit too
sour for my liking.

Nice and cheap. Came here to eat their vegetarian beehoon. It only cost me $3 for the whole plate, which is cheaper than what other places are selling them for. Other things sold here are also really cheap, but I didn't get to try them.

Tried the lontong. Nice averagely good.
Food prices are inexpensive too.
A very unassuming stall in a coffee shop but I found that the vegetarian Bee Hoon with other add-ons were flavorful.
Stall auntie is friendly, food is cheap, love their homemade curry puff!
